{
  "texts": [
    "figure 5 illustrates the distribution of the top non-English languages represented in the headlines.",
    "Korean (ko) led with over 5,000 headlines, followed by Japanese (ja) and Spanish (es) exceeding 1,000 each.",
    "Other languages like French (fr), German (de), and Indonesian (id) had moderate representation, while Vietnamese (vi), Portuguese (pt), Dutch (nl), Chinese (zh-cn), Russian (ru), and Hindi (hi) were less prevalent.",
    "English language dominated, constituting 82.3% of the corpus, highlighting a potential bias and mirroring the internet's linguistic landscape, where English is dominant.",
    "Hence our data though global, is skewed towards English language implying that our analyses on understanding the fear of AI and AI phobia propagated by news headlines is largely associated with English speaking people and nations."
  ]
}